Greetings LEIHS Students and Families!

In an effort to comply with the state’s requirement that all schools track students’ academic growth during a school year, it is necessary for all Lake Erie International High School students to complete NWEA Map Growth testing every fall, winter, and spring. These tests are not a pass/fail type of test; they are simply an indicator for us to understand each student’s academic strengths and areas of concern to help us gauge the most effective individualized instruction for each student.

Normally, MAP testing is done on computers in the school building. However, with the recent COVID-19 crisis going on, testing will be done remotely at home for at…

****DRIVE-THRU FOOD DISTRIBUTION****
Wednesday, September 2, 2020, **2:00 pm to 4:00 pm
Parma Senior High School 6285 W 54th Street | Parma, OH

* 1 box per household ** no lines before 2:00 pm

Please pre-register at www.WeFeedCLE.org.

Go to the drop-down menu and choose Parma Senior High School. You will receive a number when you register. Please bring it with you to show it as part of the check-in process.

IMPORTANT REMINDERS:

Due to safety regulations, you must be in a vehicle to receive food: NO EXCEPTIONS.
To ensure the safety of the community and our staff, we require that you
clear the trunk of your vehicle before coming to the distribution.
For safety reasons, we cannot enter anyone’s vehicle to load food.

For additional food resources, call our Help Center at 216.738.2067.

To access a map of pantries and distribution sites, go to GreaterClevelandFoodBank.org and click on the link at the top of the page.

FACETime has gone remote through Zoom!

LifeAct recognizes the unique environment students are currently facing, and with heightened levels of stress and anxiety, it’s more important than ever for students to be proactive about their mental health.

LifeAct has teamed up with our partners at Highland Springs Changes to offer a weekly chat where students will reflect on their mental health in a safe space.

A new topic will be explored every week and then students will ask questions and get real-time feedback from Jenn Reed, a certified adolescent therapist.

Here’s how it works:

Every Wednesday at 3 pm, we will explore a new topic for 30-40 minutes, during which our certified therapist will…

post_text:
Dear Students and Families:

While it has only been a few short months since the 2019-2020 school year began, the students at Lake Erie International High School have been doing a phenomenal amount of work towards their goal of graduation. With that, we are extremely excited to host our annual Open House on Tuesday, October 8, 2019, from 5:00 pm to 7:00 pm.

This is an opportunity for you to celebrate your or your child's accomplishments, tour our building and meet with the staff. We will also have our annual Title I and Federal Programs meeting, which will begin promptly at 5:00 pm for all parents interested in learning more about our Title I program and how our parents can become involved.

Parking is available behind the school building, off West 117th Street, as well as along the fence in the GFS parking lot next to our building off West 117th Street. Refreshments will be provided. If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to contact us at (216) 539-7229. We look forward to seeing you on the 8th!

Sincerely,
Tara Hullum, Principal

With that, we are extremely excited to host our annual Open House on Tuesday, October 8, 2019, from 5:00 pm to 7:00 pm.

This is an opportunity for you to celebrate your or your child's accomplishments, tour our building and meet with the staff. We will also have our annual Title I and Federal Programs meeting, which will begin promptly at 5:00 pm for all parents interested in learning more about our Title I program and how our parents can become involved.

Parking is available behind the school building, off West 117th Street, as well as along the fence in the GFS parking lot next to our building off West 117th Street. Refreshments will be provided. If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to contact us at (216) 539-7229. We look forward to seeing you on the 8th!

Sincerely,
Tara Hullum, Principal

post_text:
ATTENTION‼️
We will be doing Spirit Week Oct 7th-Oct 11th. During that week we’ll be giving out prizes, food, candy, etc. The days will go as followed:
Monday- Jersey Day
Tuesday- School Colors Day
Wednesday- Twin Day
Thursday- Neon Day
Friday- PJ Day

To earn tickets for the prizes & goodies here is the following criteria:
2 tickets for being on time (7:30:7:45)
1 ticket for coming before the doors lock (8:30)
3 tickets for getting 9 stamps
The ticket drawings will be held the following day after the day they have been given out.

Lastly, if you enroll to our school any time before or during Spirit Week you are more than welcome to participate and have the opportunity to be eligible to earn prizes, food, candy etc.
